review_blob: Poured from a bottle.  A nice thick white head forms on the pour.  Crystal clear with an orange/honey hue.  Super clear.  Head lasts and leaves plenty of lacing and legs.  Aroma is intense hops with both pine and grapefruit coming to the forefront.  Cascade and Amarillo are present.  Flavor is dominated by hops so much that I even though I know theres malt there, I have a hard time picking it up.  The honey malt provides some sweetness undertones.  Body is light and finish is extremely sharp and biting.

Poured from a bottle.  Hoppy aroma is immediately apparent as it pours a dark ruby brown.  Head is thick and long lasting leaving significant lacing and legs.  Citrus notes very apparent in the aroma with a small hint of bubblegum and caramel.  Bitterness is well balanced against the malt bill while the aroma and finishing tastes let you know its an IPA.  Finish is about perfect as well, being not too dry nor cloying.

Poured from a growler.  Nice ruby brown pour with a 1/2 inch head easily forming though carbonation seems a bit over done.  Decent amount of lacing.  Small notes of coffee and chocolate.  Slight bite at the end partly due to carbonation.  Hops are well balanced.  Overall a nice beer but not likely sessionable.

Poured from a bottle.  Amber to Ruby color with a nice thick head.  Head dissipates  within minutes to fine layer of bubbles.  Plenty of lacing and legs visible.  Massive malt smell, like a freshly mashed grains, with hints of bread and dried fruit.  Good body with only a slight bite due to carbonation.

Poured from a bottle.  Nice thick and creamy brown head that lingered longer than expected for a beer of this ABV.  Smells of chocolate, caramel, coffee, and a little bit of vanilla.  Sweetness dominates with cinnamon, vanilla, and caramel hitting the tongue first with a bit of roasted barley at the end.  Cant tell for sure, but there might be peppers in here balancing everything.  A great and complex Imperial Stout.

Poured from a growler, pale brown in color.  Instant coffee aroma and if not for the carbonation could easily be confused for iced coffee.  Small off-white head develops immediately but fully drops within a minute.  It leaves a small lacing on the edges and the high abv gives it legs.  Tastes of blended roast coffee with undertones of caramel and small bit of raisins.  Tough to gauge the bitterness with the coffee but it isnt cloying.  Probably the best coffee beer Ive had - will given even Oatmeal Breakfast Stout a run for its money.

Poured from a growler - big thick creamy brown head that slowly dissipates to nothing.  Lacing coats the glass.  Carbonation seems high both in taste and visual appearance.   Lacing will actively bubble away.  Big chunks of roasted barley in the nose leading to chocolate and coffee.  Malt and bitterness well balanced.  Slight caramel sweetness immediately countered by bitterness in the end.  No alcohol in the taste but a few sips will warm you up.  Overall, a good Imperial stout.

Poured from a growler - small white head immediately present and dissipates quickly.  Beautiful golden honey color with a little bit of chill haze.  Becomes crystal clear in hand though.  Hints of honey and malt in the aroma.  Medium body with a dry finish.  Hops not forward at all. Bready/malty flavor comes through.  Moderate carbonation.  Would be a great beer in Center Field for watching a day game.
beer_name: Carolina Brewery Sky Blue Golden Ale

review_blob: Poured from a bottle.  Nice thick head that persisted for a long while and then settled down.  Leaves beautiful lacing.  Aroma is wonderfully balanced between bourbon, vanilla, and hops.  On tasting, the bourbon is present but not overpowering.  The Vanilla and caramel undertones are more present but again, balanced with the hops.  Finishes dry but overall very smooth beer.
beer_name: Founders Backstage Series # 6: Doom Imperial IPA

review_blob: Purchased a bottle from my local growler shop.  Pours brilliantly clear, low to moderate carbonation.  Slight head that quickly dissipates.  Whiskey aroma is detectable in the undertones of the aroma but not overwhelming.  Pleasant apple taste but slightly tamer than American ciders.  Whiskey notes are pleasant.  Was expecting a bit more carbonation but doesnt detract at all.
